Create a fullstack Task Manager project using:

Frontend: Next.js (App Router)
Backend: Go serverless function for Vercel
Styling: Tailwind CSS
Database: In-memory array

The project must be deployable to Vercel directly.

====================================
BACKEND REQUIREMENTS (Go)
====================================

File location: /api/tasks.go

1. Create struct:

type Task struct {
    ID        int       `json:"id"`
    Title     string    `json:"title"`
    Status    string    `json:"status"`
    CreatedAt time.Time `json:"created_at"`
}

2. Use:
- auto increment ID
- in-memory slice

3. Implement endpoints:

GET /api/tasks
- Return all tasks
- Support optional filter:
  /api/tasks?status=Pending

POST /api/tasks
- Create new task
- Validate empty title
- Default status = "Pending"
- Return 201

PUT /api/tasks?id=1
- Update task status
- Return 404 if not found

DELETE /api/tasks?id=1
- Delete task
- Return 404 if not found

4. Add:
- CORS headers
- JSON responses
- 405 for invalid methods
- Proper error handling

====================================
FRONTEND REQUIREMENTS (Next.js App Router)
====================================

1. Create app/page.tsx

UI Requirements:

- Page title: Task Manager
- Form input for new task
- Submit button
- Dropdown filter by status:
  - All
  - Pending
  - In Progress
  - Done
- Task list card layout
- Status badge color:
  - Pending = yellow
  - In Progress = blue
  - Done = green
- Update status button
- Delete button

2. Must implement:

- useEffect to load tasks
- useState for state management
- Loading state (show spinner or text)
- Error handling UI (show red alert box)
- Confirmation dialog before delete
- Disable button while loading

3. Use fetch() for API calls.

4. Clean responsive layout using Tailwind CSS.
No external UI libraries.

====================================
TAILWIND SETUP
====================================

- Configure Tailwind properly for Next.js
- Use modern minimal clean dashboard style
- Center container
- Card shadow
- Rounded corners
- Smooth hover transitions

====================================
VERCEL CONFIG
====================================

Add vercel.json:

{
  "functions": {
    "api/*.go": {
      "runtime": "vercel-go@3.0.0"
    }
  }
}

====================================
GO MODULE
====================================

Create go.mod compatible with Go 1.22

====================================
IMPORTANT
====================================

- Code must be clean and production structured
- Separate handler logic into functions
- No external database
- Ensure project runs after:
  npm install
  vercel

Generate full project structure with all files.
